HEADWORD: Annates
<hw>An"nates</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Ann</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Eccl. Law)</fld> <def>The first year's profits of a spiritual
preferment, anciently paid by the clergy to the pope; first fruits. In
England, they now form a fund for the augmentation of poor
livings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

